How to make the code more readable:
	- use readable names for both variables and functions
	- make the functions do a single thing only
	- split the code into more files/classes

Problems:
	- when a node mines a new block, it somehow becomes more likely to be the first to mine the next several blocks
	- when an "important" node suddenly quits the network, de-sync happens
	- recent_successful_connections are accessed concurrently without a lock
	- unpickling stack underflow

Features:
	- rememberring the recent peers' addresses in order to re-connect with them on the next launch
